<Author>bucklong
<Content>Mixed Review ... Not too good though. OK ... I booked this hotel for a one-night stopover in Miami on the way to St. Maarten. I selected it because it was close to the airport and although there were some negative reviews ... the pictures looked nice enough. This hotel has seen better days. It appears that it was once on a main highway or thoroughfare and was probably built as a motor inn type accomodation. The room was clean enough ... I didn't have issues with that ... and the bed was comfortable enough for a one night stay over. The morning shuttle service to the airport was fine ... but good grief ... even after calling the hotel twice we waited about 45 minutes for the shuttle from the airport and when it finally arrived the driver PACKED it ridiculously full ... to the point that I felt it was unsafe. If the driver had to stop quickly etc. the people standing would have been toppling all over and the driver even packed luggage onto the entrance stairs of the shuttle so if people would have had to exit quickly ... there would have been no way out! It appeared that many of the guests that night had been put up by American Airlines due to flight problems and that's probably why the shuttle was overloaded. When we arrived there were about 35 people trying to check in and only one desk agent. Upon arrival ( about 9:30 pm) the hotel lobby was very nice, we checked into our room and went down to the lounge for a cocktail and hoped to have some dinner or a snack. The young man tending bar did not know how to make hardly a single drink. Mojito, anything that involved mixing was beyond him. Basically you got beer, wine, or something very simple. I could live with that but wasn't thrilled. He was pleasant enough and in his defense we were told he was filling in. He turned out to be the bus-boy at breakfast the next morning so .... We finally got frustrated and went to the raucous seafood eaterie next door and had great drinks and it looked like they had good food but we didn't eat. The next morning we were up early for our shuttle to the airport and went to breakfast at the restaurant. Terrible. It was buffet only and for $10 you could have cereal, juice, toast, and coffee. For an extra $5 you could have fresh fruit, and some hot items, none of which were very good and a couple of which were unidentifiable and basically inedible. It was weird because the waiters were wearing tuxedos and there were nice linens etc. and yet the food was worse than you would find at a local buffet for $7.99 where I live. It seems like this hotel is run by a family ... all of the people that were working at night were also there early in the morning ... and I certainly don't begrudge a hard working family for trying to make a living ... but I think they get most of their business from American Airlines putting people up after flight delays/canellations ... and those travellers don't have a choice so the service reflects that. All in all ... this hotel met my needs ... all I needed was a stopover for a night that was close to the airport. But I would DEFINATELY not book this accomodation as a destination hotel in the Miami area. As a side note ... the pool area looked quite nice but I wasn't in a position to take a swim or anything. 
