<Content>A Dump, Do Yourself A Favour Avoid At All Costs This hotel doesn't even deserve a one star rating. What a hole. The staff are rude which ads insult to injury. We stayed in this kip on the 30th Dec as we had an early enough flight and had to leave are car hire back and thought it would be convenient, never again would I stay here or advise anyone else to either. Use the Mariott across the road. There is no tea/coffee facilities in the rooms, it doesn't do room service, the key chain on our door was broken, we were in room 521, both lifts were broken when we stayed and had to use the service lift, after been told by a foreign guy who worked there that the stairs were a no go!!!!!!I was trying to contact the reception for an hour and the guy at reception kept picking up the phone and hanging up again, I made a complaint to him and he just shrugged his shoulders and said 'So' There was only two towels in the bathroom, and the room was filty. Music was blarring from some pub nearby until 1.30am, we got sod all sleep. I can safely say its the worst hotel I have ever stayed in and we tried to get another hotel to stay in when we were there, but unfortunately as it was the 30th Dec couldn't get any, we even considered sleeping in the car. Do yourselves a favour and stay somewhere else if at all possible, The Marriott or somewhere else, but don't put yourself through such horrors. You've been warned and you will be treated like dirt. 
