<Author>BGARDENLOVER
<Content>Ok For A Quick Stopover We rolled into this hotel at the end of a cruise which terminated in Port Miami. We used the hotel as a daybase. Our flight did not leave Miami until 8pm. We arrived at hotel at 10AM and only used it as a dayroom until our flight left.We chose the hotel because of its close proximity to the airport and reasonable cost.The room we had, 424 I believe, was ok. It was clean and the bathroom was clean as well. We had two double beds. Air-conditioning worked. We slept a few hours and then went to the pool, which I thought was pretty nice for that hotel. See pics on Travel Advisor.We called the front desk twice for extra towels due to our time at the pool. Looks like they just issue a few towels per room. Our requests were quickly answered by a knock on the door with a maid handing us more towels. The hotel has a free shuttle to the airport -- which we took advantage of. I think it also offers a shuttle to port, possibly with a charge for more than two persons. Check other reviews on that.The hotel also has a nice lobby and what looks like an expensive restaurant serving South American cuisine which we did not frequent. There is a sub shop across the street that is not bad, but double-check your order. They got ours all botched up. There is also a sit-down restaurant next-door, which we also did not try. The hotel is located on a busy street just a few miles from the airport. The planes do go over the hotel constantly, so if that would bother you, don't stay there.All in all, not a bad place to land for a few hours. It is by no means however, a Ritz-Carlton but ok for a quick stopover while waiting for a cruise or flight. 
