<Content>Horrible, Dirty and mildew February 16, 2006I have never experienced such filth and improper care for a room as I had in this hotel. Upon arriving I requested a non-smoking room.February 15th I arrived to a very nice looking lobby, however came into a room that had mildew in the walls and the bathrooms have a permanent stain on the tub and floor which looked as an oil stain and down right filth. In plain view cigarette burns through out the room and linens. I was on a very tight schedule and did not have the time to deal with a room change therefore all I did was to leave my luggage and go to my appointments for the day. Upon my return at around 9:00PM I could not stay in such a room all I kept on seeing all around me was the mildew and the dirt imbedded in the carpet, comforter and curtains etc. I called the front desk and requested a room change. This room change was done from room 411 to room 202. To my surprise the room was in a worst condition. This was a handicapped room again it was so late that I had to leave early the following morning I had to stay with no other choice. I asked is there another room cleaner than this. Room 202 has the similar items mildew in the walls and around the grout in addition it has cigarette burns on the comforter and in the carpets as well as the curtains. The handicapped equipment was in plain view not under any cover or in a proper storage area, the hand rail that was in the bathroom was very rusty and filth around the edges clearly not a clean room. Again I asked to be changed to a proper room. I was given room 616 this room looked as if it was not vacuumed with drywall dust all around the edges of the room in the carpet.I had enough and at 8:00PM on February 16, I left your hotel to another hotel that offered clean beds and clean rooms. I did not receive a clean room from all aspect and any standards. In speaking to the front desk personnel they stated that they have had this issue with unclean rooms in a consistent 