<Content>Airport Regency Hotel - Miami A friend and I stayed here for one night pre-cruise in January. They had a free shuttle from the airport to the hotel. You have to flag them down to stop for you. Check in was easy. We arrived early afternoon and were given a room even tho check in was not till later in the day. We wanted to relax by the pool, but that was roped off and not available. So we opted to find something to eat. Hotel restaurant was not open so we asked at the desk for some suggestions and they pointed us to a few places. Walked down the street to the Cuban Cafe. Prices were inexpensive, food pretty good. They also had a breakfast menu which was good because when we went to the hotel restaurant for breakfast the next morning, we found it to be very expensive. The room itself was ok. Two comfortable beds, tv - all the basics. The a/c unit was noisy during the night. My friend wanted to soak in the tub after a long day and found no plug - took shower instead. Hotel offered two trips to the cruise pier(complimentary)in the morning. All in all the hotel was ok; price was reasonable, room was clean, but I wouldn't make it my home base if I was staying longer than one or two nights. 
